<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB01909</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT AMENDING SECTIONS 4, 5, 20, 22, 25, 27, 28, 34, 40, 50, 73, 112, 117, 119, 203, 204, 222, 237, 237-A, 255, 256, 257, 258, 260, 261, 262, 263, 264, 265, 266, 275, 282, 290 AND ADDING SECTIONS 6-A AND A NEW TITLE XIII UNDER THE NATIONAL INTERNAL REVENUE CODE OF 1997, AS AMENDED, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to lower the corporate tax rate through rationalizing the administration of tax incentives which shall be performance-based, target, time-bound and transparent.

Aims to widen the corporate tax base and plug its tax leakages; and to rationalize and discipline tax incentives to ensure the benefits investments would bring and help alleviate financial burden on the business community, especially the micro, small, and medium-sized enterprises.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>VILLAFUERTE, LUIS RAYMUND &quot;LRAY&quot; JR F.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-10</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB04157</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON WAYS AND MEANS ON 2019-07-24</td></tr></table>